# corpus.md.example

This is the voice corpus for `lead-magnet-creator`. Rename to `corpus.md`
and fill with 2-4 anchor lead magnets in your brand voice so the skill
produces magnets that sound like YOU.

The cover and the close borrow your `linkedin-copywriter` corpus voice
(AUTHOR voice). The body uses an operator-playbook register (OPERATOR
voice) anchored on the magnets you list below.

---

## How to populate

Two paths:

**Path A · You have an existing vault.** Link or paste 2-4 of your
strongest lead magnets here. Cover headlines, opening paragraphs, closing
CTAs, the rhythm of a body section. The skill learns voice + format taste
from these.

**Path B · You're starting from scratch.** Skip this file for the first
run. The skill will use the generic OPERATOR-voice defaults from
`SKILL.md`. Once you've shipped 2-3 magnets, fill this file with your own
voice anchors so future magnets compound.

---

## Anchor format

Use this template, one block per magnet. 2-4 anchors is the sweet spot.
More than 6 dilutes the signal.

---

### Anchor NN · <Magnet Title> · <Format>

**Cover headline:** [the two-line hero pattern verbatim]

**Opening paragraph:** [verbatim · the first 4-8 sentences the reader
sees after the cover. This is the empathy / why-listen-to-me beat.]

**One body section header:** [verbatim · pick the strongest "outcome
promise" header from the magnet. Pattern: `[Verb] your [thing] into a
[desirable outcome]` or `[Outcome] + [mechanism]`.]

**One body bullet block:** [verbatim · a 3-5 line bullet block that
shows your bullet rhythm, the symbols you use (`-`, `→`, `•`), and the
density per bullet.]

**Closing CTA:** [verbatim · the last 2-4 lines including the Cal link
and email.]

**Format used:** Notion / Google Doc / PDF / Sheet / Skills repo /
GitHub starter / GPT / Web tool / Video / Vault bundle.

**Why this magnet works:** [1-2 sentences. The structural move that
made it land · empathy opener, the verbatim prompt, the two-tier
framing, the small-numbers list.]

---

## Voice rules to extract from your anchors

Once you have 2-4 anchors filled in, write a short list at the bottom of
this file naming the patterns the skill should reuse. Examples to look
for:

- Outcome-promise section headers vs feature-label headers
- Empathy-then-receipts opener (pain → timeline → why-listen-to-me →
  payoff)
- Stats blocks formatted as ranges with a "not exact science" disclaimer
- Two-tier framings ("safe option" + "stronger option, recommended")
- Step-by-step setup with `Step N: [outcome]` headers, screenshots, and
  one "where most people mess up" line per step
- Verbatim ChatGPT system prompts on a dedicated page (radical
  generosity)
- Closing CTA pattern: `Stuck? [book / hit me up] :)` then Cal link then
  email
- Self-aware honesty lines ("nobody cares about your hospitality job at
  17", "I don't have a world-class personal brand", "let's be honest")
- Rule of small numbers: 2 pillars, 3 things, 5 guides. Never 7. Never
  10.
- Definition-then-correction openers ("Your LinkedIn profile is not a
  CV. It's a landing page.")

The goal of this file is **a reader could read the anchors and write a
new magnet that feels like you wrote it.** If the anchors don't pass that
test, swap them.

---

## Slop scrub (cross-skill, applies regardless of corpus state)

Run before report-done on any drafted magnet. Even with no anchors, the
slop scrub still runs.

**Punctuation:**
- No em dash (`—`). Hard ban. Replace with `.`, `,`, `:`, `()`, or `·`.
- No curly quotes. Straight only.
- No ellipsis (`…`). Use `...` if used at all.
- No non-breaking spaces, no en dashes used as ranges in prose.

**Banned phrases / words** (mirror your `linkedin-copywriter` blacklist):
delve · dive into · embark · unlock · unleash · harness · elevate ·
transform · revolutionize · foster · navigate · journey · landscape ·
realm · ecosystem · tapestry · paradigm · pivotal · crucial · vital ·
essential · meticulous · leverage · utilize · optimize · streamline ·
empower · amplify · spearhead · resonate · illuminate · shed light ·
beacon · testament · treasure trove · symphony · notably · arguably ·
indeed · in today's fast-paced world · at its core · it's worth noting ·
a testament to · game changer · move the needle · cutting-edge ·
state-of-the-art · seamless · world-class · scalable · robust ·
powerful · innovative · take a moment to · trust the process.

Fixes: "use" not "leverage", "help" not "empower", "strong" not "robust",
"big" not "transformative", "show" not "underscore", "many parts" not
"multifaceted".

**Structural slop:**
- No TL;DR / Key takeaways / In summary headers. The magnet is the
  takeaway.
- Max one negation pivot per magnet ("It's not X. It's Y.").
- No throat-clearing transitions: Furthermore · Moreover · Additionally
  · That said · Importantly · Ultimately · Subsequently.
- No bold/italics fake formatting via Unicode characters.
- No keycap emoji as numbered headers (1️⃣ 2️⃣ 3️⃣). Use plain `1)` or
  `Step 1`.
- No symmetric paragraphs (every paragraph the same length). Real
  paragraphs are uneven.

---

## Refresh

Re-read this file before drafting any new magnet. If a new magnet ships
that earns big engagement, lift its strongest section openers into a
new anchor and refresh this file. Quarterly cadence is fine.
